description: Imports a model that has been trained successfully.

parameters.name: SourceModelVersionArn
parameters.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the model version to import.

parameters.name: DatasetName
parameters.description: The name of the dataset for the machine learning model being imported.

parameters.name: LabelsInputConfiguration
parameters.description: Contains the configuration information for the S3 location being used to hold label data. S3InputConfiguration (dict) --- Contains location information for the S3 location being used for label data. The name of the S3 bucket holding the label data. Prefix (string) --- The prefix for the S3 bucket used for the label data. LabelGroupName (string) --- The name of the label group to be used for label data.

nested_params.name: S3InputConfiguration
nested_params.description: Contains location information for the S3 location being used for label data.

nested_params.name: Bucket
nested_params.description: The name of the S3 bucket holding the label data.

nested_params.name: Prefix
nested_params.description: The prefix for the S3 bucket used for the label data.

nested_params.name: LabelGroupName
nested_params.description: The name of the label group to be used for label data.

parameters.name: ClientToken
parameters.description: A unique identifier for the request. If you do not set the client request token, Amazon Lookout for Equipment generates one. This field is autopopulated if not provided.

parameters.name: Tags
parameters.description: The tags associated with the machine learning model to be created. (dict) --- A tag is a key-value pair that can be added to a resource as metadata. The key for the specified tag. The value for the specified tag.

nested_params.name: Key
nested_params.description: The key for the specified tag.

nested_params.name: Value
nested_params.description: The value for the specified tag.

parameters.name: InferenceDataImportStrategy
parameters.description: Indicates how to import the accumulated inference data when a model version is imported. The possible values are as follows: NO_IMPORT --- Don't import the data. ADD_WHEN_EMPTY --- Only import the data from the source model if there is no existing data in the target model. OVERWRITE --- Import the data from the source model and overwrite the existing data in the target model.
